column5: Heading down to the smoke in the morning. Have smoked meat to pick up,and fishing is in the plans,along with picking up a few fishing items. I want to get a Lowrance ice trasducer. From what I have seen online,West marine has the best price..  Another question,do  ice trasducers come with the floating foam,or does it just hang in the hole? That didnt sound right,but hey. Any help here would be nice. Thanks B
Got mine at radioworld. I think it was $90 for the ducer and the power cord together. Doesnt come with foam. I just used some pipe insulation and some zip ties.  Works great
Are they still at their port credit location? I,m dating myself here.
Steeles, a few yards east of 400 on the south side
Thanks Brian. It,s along my home path.
Thanks Raf. I,ll be right around the corner from them. I was planning on stopping in there, on my travels.
Generally a hard item to find in stock in the GTA.. but a slow ice year you may get lucky. Should have ordered on Ebay and it would have been in your mailbox already!
Ya I was there Wayne. Check out the prices? NUTZ
I got mine for less than $60 last year...
Cabela's Canada Price $54.88 Shipping and handling Charges $14.95 Taxes &  Duty $13.34 Fees (Broker) $3.50  Order Total $86.67 at your front door

No clue but thats what i payed for mine
$79.99 at Fishing World in Hamilton...for the blue connector ice ducer.
